<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11115a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11115a">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11115a"> 115(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mary&nbsp;(m) of James </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: That is, Mary of Cleophas (in the Authorised Version), but more accurately &lsquo;of Clopas&rsquo;, that is, the wife of Clopas. In the New Testament she first appears standing before the cross (John 19:25) and then by Christ&apos;s tomb (Matthew 27:61; Mark 15:47). She had four sons: James, Joses, Jude and Simon. She is also thought to have been a sister of the Virgin Mary. </mm> </dd></dl>
